The Christian community in Kaduna State embarked on a protest marchfollowing the killing of a Baptist Church cleric, Rev. AlhamduMangadus.Mangadus was reportedly killed by gunmen suspected to be bandits.The gunmen had reportedly trailed the cleric to his farm in Jema’alocal council area in southern Kaduna where he was killed.State chairman of the Christian Association of Nigeria (CAN), Rev.Joseph Hayab, said: “Gunmen killed Rev. Alhamdu Mangadus of BaptistChurch, Asso (in Jema’a Council), today (September 11)."He was shot and killed on his farm and they injured another fellow from Tanda.”According to Hayab, the cleric’s corpse was taken to an unknown destination.